.\" bgpucap man page — BrightDate GPU/CPU/memory capture for Apple Silicon
.TH BGPUCAP 1 2026-05-30 "gpucap 0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bgpucap \- run a command and report GPU, CPU, and unified memory usage
.br
gpucap \- alias for \fBbgpucap\fR (Homebrew installs a symlink)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bgpucap
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR...]
.PP
.B bgpucap
.B gpuexercise
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bgpucap
runs
.I COMMAND
with its arguments, polls system metrics while the child runs, then prints
average and peak GPU, CPU, and unified memory utilization to stderr.
Exit status matches the child process.
.PP
The crate is named \fBgpucap\fR; the BrightDate ecosystem command is
\fBbgpucap\fR (like \fBbtime\fR for \fBtime\fR).
.PP
Apple Silicon Macs only (M1/M2/M3/M4 and later, arm64).
Intel Macs and non-macOS platforms are not supported.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Print statistics using a
.I FORMAT
string (plain text; no color).
See
.B FORMAT SPECIFIERS
below.
.TP
.BR \-\-interval " " \fIMS\fR
Sampling interval in milliseconds (default: 100).
.TP
.BR \-\-color " [=" \fIWHEN\fR "]"
Colorize the default human report:
.BR auto ", " always ", " never ", " plain ", " ansi ", or " truecolor
(default:
.BR auto ).
Ignored when
.B \-\-format
is set.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-color
Disable color output.
.TP
.BR \-\-color\-scheme " " \fISCHEME\fR
Color palette:
.BR default " or " bright
(default:
.BR default ).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version.
.SS gpuexercise subcommand
Generate sustained GPU load for testing via a Metal compute shader.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-percent " " \fIPCT\fR
Target GPU utilization 1-100 (default: 50).
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-seconds " " \fISEC\fR
Duration in seconds (default: 10).
.PP
Also accepts
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format
and the color options above.
.SH FORMAT SPECIFIERS
When
.B \-\-format
or
.B BGPUCAP_FORMAT
is set, output is always plain text.
Specifiers follow BrightDate
.BR btime \-f
conventions where applicable.
.PP
Full reference:
.RS
https://github.com/Digital-Defiance/brightdate-rust/blob/main/FORMAT-SPEC.md
.RE
.TP
.B %gA \fR/\fB %gP
GPU average / peak percent (one decimal, no % suffix).
.TP
.B %uA \fR/\fB %uP
CPU average / peak percent (system-wide).
.TP
.B %hA \fR/\fB %hP
Unified memory average / peak percent.
.TP
.B %tG
Exercise target GPU percent (\fBgpuexercise\fR only).
.TP
.B %e \fR/\fB %E \fR/\fB %B \fR/\fB %b \fR/\fB %dE
Elapsed time (seconds, h:mm:ss, BrightDate days, millidays).
.TP
.B %Ws \fR/\fB %N
Command start BrightDate (9 decimal places, days since J2000.0).
.TP
.B %Wt \fR/\fB %n
Command end BrightDate.
.TP
.B %C
Command line.
.TP
.B %x
Child exit status.
.PP
Default machine format (ends with a newline):
.RS
%gA,%gP,%uA,%uP,%hA,%hP,%e,%Ws,%Wt
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BGPUCAP_FORMAT
Format string (same as
.BR \-f ;
.B GPUCAP_FORMAT
still accepted).
.TP
.B BGPUCAP_COLOR \fR/\fB BGPUCAP_COLOR_SCHEME
Color settings (\fBGPUCAP_*\fR still accepted).
.TP
.B NO_COLOR \fR/\fB CLICOLOR \fR/\fB CLICOLOR_FORCE
Standard color control variables.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit status of
.I COMMAND
on normal termination, or 126/127 if the command could not be executed.
.SH EXAMPLES
Wrap a command (colored report on TTY):
.RS
.EX
bgpucap ffmpeg -i in.mp4 out.mp4
.EE
.RE
.PP
Machine-readable CSV with BrightDate timestamps:
.RS
.EX
bgpucap -f '%gA,%gP,%uA,%uP,%hA,%hP,%e,%Ws,%Wt' sleep 1
.EE
.RE
.PP
GPU exerciser at 50% for 10 seconds:
.RS
.EX
bgpucap gpuexercise --percent 50 --seconds 10
.EE
.RE
.SH METRICS
.TP
GPU
IOKit \fIDevice Utilization %\fR (IOReport fallback).
.TP
CPU
Mach \fIhost_processor_info\fR (system-wide).
.TP
Memory
Unified RAM via \fIhost_statistics64\fR and \fIhw.memsize\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR btime (1),
.BR time (1)
.PP
